Body: Description: Hello, I need assistance with collecting sensitive data on my file server. I'm able to successfully collect activity, permissions, and other general information. However, when it comes to sensitive data, the application encounters several errors. In the "SEEK System Scans" job, I receive the following message: Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.AppletDeployment | No need to scan, Tier 2 DB USN is greater than Tier 1 DB USN, needs bulk import. Based on the documentation, I unchecked the two boxes under the query in "Scan Settings" — "Restart Incomplete Scans after" and "Rescan unimported hosts after" — but the same error persists. I also tried changing the hosts, using the local server, and selecting all hosts, but none of these approaches worked. In the "SEEK Bulk Import" job, which should be running, I consistently get the following error: Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess | Sequence contains no elements. I’ve attempted changing the hosts here as well, but the issue remains the same. Note: I recently upgraded Netwrix Access Analyzer to version 12.0, and I couldn’t find the Sensitive Data Discovery module in this version. Could you please assist me with this case? I’ve attached the error logs generated in the output folders for your review. Thank you in advance. Best regards, Gustavo Rossato

This one may required an escalation.

I would probably try to copy the T2 from the proxy and replace after backing up the t2 on the NAA App server.

Then attempt an import to start.

Make sure debug is one.

What We've Learned Updated: The customer is having issues collecting Sensitive Data. He's getting an error that the T2 DB is greater than the T1 DB.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Launch the Netwrix Analyzer application
Expand the File System group
Expand 0.Collection group
Select the SEEK System Scan and run
